Package io.storj

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ApiKey
    Represents an access credential to certain resources.
    Bucket
    Represents a stateful resource to a bucket in a project.
    BucketCreateOption
    Options for creating new buckets.
    BucketInfo
    Represents bucket metadata.
    BucketListOption
    Options for listing buckets.
    Caveat
    Represents a set of restriction to apply to ApiKeys and Scopes.
    Caveat.Builder
    Builder for Caveat objects.
    EncryptionAccess
    Represents an encryption access context.
    EncryptionParameters
    Represents the encryption parameters used for encrypting the data on the network.
    EncryptionParameters.Builder
    Builder for EncryptionParameters objects.
    EncryptionRestriction
    Represents a restriction to the access of objects based on a path prefix.
    Key
    Represents the largest key used by any encryption protocol.
    ObjectInfo
    Represents object metadata.
    ObjectInputStream
    An InputStream for reading data from an object stored on the Storj network.
    ObjectListOption
    Options for listing objects.
    ObjectOutputStream
    An OutputStream for writing data to an object stored on the Storj network.
    ObjectUploadOption
    Options for uploading objects.
    Project
    Represents a stateful resource to a project on a satellite.
    RedundancyScheme
    Represents the redundancy scheme used for erasure encoding data on the network.
    RedundancyScheme.Builder
    Builder for RedundancyScheme objects.
    Scope
    Represents all credentials you need to access data on the Storj network: Satellite address in the form of "host:port" ApiKey to access the satellite EncryptionAccess for accessing the encrypted content
    Uplink
    Represents the main entrypoint to the Storj network.
    UplinkOption
    Options for configuring Uplink.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    CipherSuite
    Enumeration of the cipher suites supported by Storj libraries for encrypting the object paths and the data stored on the network.
    RedundancyAlgorithm
    Enumeration of the redundancy algorithms supported by Storj libraries for erasure encoding the data stored on the network.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    StorjException
    Signals that an exception occurred when calling a method of the Storj library.
